--- USW_TS3_TS5 ---

Umbrella-sampling stage connecting TS3 and TS5 (see ../README), seeded from
../SMD_TS3_TS5/<rep>/lmp_files/ and restrained on 'cobh'. Same layout as ../USW_TS3_TS4/: 100
window subfolders per replica ('000'-'099'), each with a static harmonic restraint
(KAPPA=300 kcal/mol/A^2) centered on its own cobh value spanning 1.9-2.7 in even steps
('generate_US_window.py'); 'inputs/lmp_files/' is the traceability copy of the seed
structures; 'WHAM/' holds the per-replica WHAM reconstruction ('fepTS3_TS5_pph4.out' plus
diagnostic plots) — see PMF_react_TS1/USW_100_react_TS1/README for the full per-window/WHAM
file description, substituting the coordinate name.

As in ../USW_TS3_TS4/, a top-level 'average_PMF.py' averages the three replicas'
'fepTS3_TS5_pph4.out' profiles into 'average_pmf_noerror.dat' and 'average_pmf.png'
(labelled TS3->TS5, x-axis 'C_LG'), with per-point error bars and the same relative-minimum
annotation logic.

Three replicas (rep1/2/3) — one README covers all three.

Note: this README documents pre-existing content; no existing file was modified.
